## Results

### Learning Curve
The agent converges from near-zero to near-optimal reward (~9.8/10) within ~200 episodes.

![Learning Curve](results/learning_curve.png)

### RPE Dynamics — The Dopamine Signal
Early in training, large prediction errors drive learning. As the agent improves, δ → 0.

![RPE Dynamics](results/rpe_dynamics.png)

### Temporal Transfer of the Dopamine Signal
**The key neuroscience result:** As training progresses, the RPE signal *transfers backward in time* — from the reward delivery state (US/goal) toward the conditioned stimulus (CS zone). This mirrors Schultz et al. (1997) exactly.

![Temporal Transfer](results/temporal_transfer.png)

### Value Function Evolution
The state value map V(s) = maxₐ Q(s,a) develops from uniform to goal-directed over training.

