## Environment: Pavlovian Grid

A 5×5 gridworld designed to mirror classical conditioning paradigms:

```
S  .  .  .  .
.  .  .  .  .
.  .  .  .  .
.  .  .  .  .
X  .  .  C  G
```

| Cell | Role | Reward |
|------|------|--------|
| `S` | Start | — |
| `G` | Goal (Unconditioned Stimulus) | +10 |
| `C` | CS zone (Conditioned Stimulus) | +0.5 |
| `X` | Trap | −5 |
| `.` | Empty | −0.1 (step cost) |

